# Notification System Design

## Stage 1: REST API Design & Contract

### Core Actions Identified

1. **Fetch Notifications** - Retrieve notifications with optional filters
2. **Mark as Read** - Update notification read status
3. **Delete Notification** - Remove notification
4. **Get Priority Notifications** - Retrieve top N important notifications
5. **Subscribe to Real-time Updates** - Establish real-time connection

### REST API Endpoints

#### 1. Get All Notifications
```
GET /api/notifications
Query Parameters:
  - limit: number (default: 10, max: 100)
  - page: number (default: 1)
  - notification_type: string (Event | Result | Placement)

Request Headers:
  Authorization: Bearer <token>
  Content-Type: application/json

Response (200 OK):
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "notifications": [
      {
        "id": "uuid",
        "type": "Placement|Result|Event",
        "message": "string",
        "timestamp": "2026-04-22T17:51:30Z",
        "isRead": boolean,
        "createdAt": "2026-04-22T17:51:30Z"
      }
    ],
    "pagination": {
      "currentPage": 1,
      "totalPages": 10,
      "totalItems": 100,
      "itemsPerPage": 10
    }
  },
  "message": "Notifications retrieved successfully"
}
```

#### 2. Mark Notification as Read
```
PATCH /api/notifications/{id}/read
Request Body:
{
  "isRead": true
}

Request Headers:
  Authorization: Bearer <token>
  Content-Type: application/json

Response (200 OK):
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "id": "uuid",
    "isRead": true,
    "updatedAt": "2026-04-22T17:51:30Z"
  },
  "message": "Notification marked as read"
}
```

#### 3. Mark Multiple Notifications as Read
```
PATCH /api/notifications/read-bulk
Request Body:
{
  "notificationIds": ["uuid1", "uuid2", "uuid3"]
}

Response (200 OK):
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "updatedCount": 3,
    "timestamp": "2026-04-22T17:51:30Z"
  },
  "message": "Notifications marked as read"
}
```

#### 4. Delete Notification
```
DELETE /api/notifications/{id}

Response (200 OK):
{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Notification deleted successfully"
}
```

#### 5. Get Priority Notifications (Top N)
```
GET /api/notifications/priority
Query Parameters:
  - limit: number (default: 10, max: 50)
  - notification_type: string (Event | Result | Placement) [optional]

Response (200 OK):
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "priorityNotifications": [
      {
        "id": "uuid",
        "type": "Placement",
        "message": "string",
        "timestamp": "2026-04-22T17:51:30Z",
        "isRead": boolean,
        "priority": 3,
        "score": 95.5
      }
    ]
  },
  "message": "Priority notifications retrieved"
}
```

#### 6. Real-time Notifications (WebSocket)
```
Connection: ws://localhost:8000/api/notifications/stream
Authorization: Bearer <token>

Message Format (Server to Client):
{
  "event": "notification:new",
  "data": {
    "id": "uuid",
    "type": "Placement",
    "message": "string",
    "timestamp": "2026-04-22T17:51:30Z"
  }
}

Alternative: Server-Sent Events (SSE)
GET /api/notifications/stream
Response: text/event-stream

data: {"id": "uuid", "type": "Placement", ...}
```

### Real-time Notification Mechanism

**Chosen Approach: WebSocket + Server-Sent Events (SSE)**

- **WebSocket** for bi-directional communication and active subscriptions
- **SSE** as fallback for simpler one-way updates
- **Rationale**: WebSocket provides true real-time, low-latency delivery; SSE provides automatic reconnection
- **Implementation**: Use Socket.io for WebSocket abstraction with automatic fallbacks

### Error Response Format
```json
{
  "success": false,
  "error": {
    "code": "INVALID_REQUEST",
    "message": "Descriptive error message",
    "details": {}
  },
  "timestamp": "2026-04-22T17:51:30Z"
}
```

